annotation.TEXT: Okay, let's start off with Yoshi's House I guess.
To be continued...
Argh! I screwed up my turkey spin jump.
Good, now keep those turkeys locked up in maximum security pens, please!
Huh? How do I advance the message? ...Oh!
Yes! The game mercifully let me past that guy without any problem!
Man, it's acting like a Goomba. This is gonna be tricky. (Now I see why the barns were made to be reset doors.)
Ah, so Diana is just a vine with different graphics. I was wondering how that ladder-building would work...
Ooh, and this whole sentence (which lacks a period) must be important, so remember: "Barns act as reset doors"!
Also: Green and isolated.
Well, that's interesting. Okay, I guess I'm outta here!
Yeah, I thought so. Looks like this special chicken was made unable to collide with any other enemy, which is nice, because you know how fragile Goombas normally are!
I wonder what the point of this secret passage really is...
Okay, so I've got three levels I could explore here, but where shall I begin? Hmm...
Whoa, hello! I found a secret passage, but where does it lead?
Oh, man. How serious could it be? Well, obviously serious enough that the game had to warn me about it!
Ouch... Why would those turkeys be resting there?! Okay, they're chickens, but they're evil chickens!
D'oh! Them turkeys are killing me, man!
Okay, through a completely arbitrary and random method involving one of the Blocks That Matter, I have decided to go with Barnyard Mayhem!
Ah, so I've finally found my target. Wait, I've gotta stomp it to stun it?

Well, how about I let you guys, the viewers, decide? Place your votes for which level I should play next in the comments and I will start with the one with the most votes next time! (In case of a tie, I'll pick one at random.)
Oh, come on... Hit the guy, already! GAAAMMMEEE!!!
Holy... How the crap did I not get brutally murdered there?!
The turkeys have clearly completely taken over the land to the right, so there's no choice but to go back to the left.
AHHH!!! What was that?! Some sort of evil cow?! Well, anyway, I guess the level's just gonna end on that note.
Can I... not talk to Joshi here? Oh, well. Also, avoid the stray dogs... or stomp them. Whatever works.
Also, only the normal turn blocks can be broken. It seems kind of odd to arbitrarily switch between normal turn blocks and unturnable ones.
Okay, I know this music. It's Mabe Village from Link's Awakening.
Okay, well, let's start with mission one, which is nice enough to let the player know that the coin value will reset.
Okay, so collect 30 chickens, the trained chicken Diana can build ladders, watch out for stray animals, and do NOT TOUCH the red chickens! Got it.
Okay, those are all solid.
Man, this one looks tricky to get.
Man... Now I gotta backtrack. My brain probably farted again and didn't spot two obvious ones...
Can I stand on those question marks?
Oh, man. This part... And I know there's a chomp turkey just on the other side...
Now, how the heck am I gonna get past this guy? Well, I could hope for one more miracle...
Oh, god... A chomp turkey... I'm going to go way up and over it if I can.
This hack was made by Snifit, who was one of the makers of EVW (Where's Aquamentus?), and some time ago, TheGoomba98 suggested this hack to me, so here we go!
I wonder what this music is? (It's Harvest Moon SNES - New Year's Festival. Thanks, NoctournalDonut!) Also, apparently, we've got a mission select screen. Interesting...
Okay, remember those important highlighted keywords: Lab, most, deadly, touch.
Huh. So, certain turn blocks actually turn, but others don't. Also, note how most of the blocks don't have rounded corners, though a spinning turn block does, at least while it's spinning.
And, at this point I'm thinking for a moment that maybe I should've split these two missions into separate recordings, but...
Hey turkeys, stop disguising yourselves as chickens!
Okay, I'm done dealing with the turkeys. Now, I've got two levels left to choose from. Which one should I play next? Switchless Castle, or MarioTropics?
Yeah, I could use some sleep after all that. Good night... Zzzzz...
Seriously! Go away, freaking turkey!
Anything beyond the goal? Doesn't look like it.
I know this music too. It's Kirby's Block Ball - Stage 1.
No secret passage here anymore...
Hello, this is SomeGuy712x, and welcome to...
Okay, I have all 30. Now let's get out of here!
Oh, geez... Well, at least my chicken doesn't get destroyed by hitting the chomp turkeys.
Anything in this barn? No, I guess not.
Oh, wait. There's the two chickens down there! How do I reach them? Ohh... There's gotta be another secret passage.
Okay, that mission is done, but there's still another mission left to do in that level, so let's be like Nike and just do it.
Nope. The bouncing ones are not slide-killable. Now I know.
Well, those chickens look green, but I can tell it's just a disguise. See, if you stomp on any of them, the whole group turns red!
Oh, come on!
Okay, so I'm apparently off screen and can move left or right to scroll the text. (That probably should've been mentioned somewhere, as I didn't know that at first.)
Man, has the turkey population exploded or something here?
Yep, and the screen actually scrolls up. Can I get it to scroll up further?
Oh, hey there, Diana. How's it going?
Finally! Man, that one chicken was starting to make me go cucco!
Whoa! That was close! I did not see that pit coming there!
Man, is it that door-to-door salesman trying to sell me those vacuums again?
Oh, my god! So many turkeys!
So those must be the red chickens that I was told not to touch. They move like parakoopas, but spin jumps don't destroy them (but at least I can bounce off of them with spin jumps).
Well, I can see why the coin counter needed to be reset for this mission. It's now basically a chicken counter!
Nothing really happens on the title screen, so let's just begin the game!
Hey, white chickens, get away from those turkeys! (I'm just gonna call the evil chickens turkeys from now on.)
Oh, now, I bet these chickens act like munchers, so I shouldn't touch them at all! Also, can I slide-kill the bouncing ones?
Oh, man. The shaded part made it seem like it would go straight down there, but actually, it just comes out of this wall here, where a player could easily fall into the pit if they're not careful.

Uh, oh... Possible problem with the level found. If this turn block is broken too soon, it would become very difficult to get on the highest ledge here and reach one of the chickens. (Max speed jumping could still get a player up there, but it would be tricky.)
Huh, the wiggler turkeys pass through my chicken unimpeded?
There's the goal, but I guess this barrier won't let me pass until I've gotten 30 chickens, and I only have 28 right now. Where did I miss two?
Okay, so the choices are... Switchless Castle, Barnyard Mayhem, and MarioTropics.
Yep. So, I guess maybe that first secret passage was meant to just let the player know about their existence. (Though, I probably wouldn't have put that one's exit right next to a pit...)
Okay, that's good. I didn't mysteriously warp to the bonus game room when I jumped during the intro here!
So many narrow escapes...
Ooh, a hidden 1-up! At first it looked like there were only turkeys up here, but I had a hunch there was something else, and I was right!
Ahh!!! Chomp turkey! Leave me alone!
So, is this like the same level, but set at a later time of day, possibly after the 30-chicken round up I just did?
